         <abstract>
            <p>We study uniform error estimates of operational quadrature methods for nonlinear convolution equations on the half-line. Equations of this kind arise in control engineering and diffusion problems. The essential ingredients are the stability of the operational quadrature method in an $L^2$ setting, which is inherited from the continuous equation by its very construction, and a theorem that says that the behavior of the linearized equations is the same in all $L^p$ spaces $(1 \leq p \leq \infty)$.</p>
          </abstract>
